com.pega.pegarules.pub.generator

Interface PageDescriptor


  • public interface PageDescriptor
    The PageDescriptor interface identifies the information that is known about a ClipboardPage during First-Use Assembly processing.

    • Method Detail

      • getPageName

        java.lang.String getPageName()
        Returns the name if this page, if it is known during First-Use Assembly.
        Returns:
        name of this page, if it is known, or an empty String if this page is anonymous (including embedded pages), or null if no information about the class of this page is available.

      • getClassName

        java.lang.String getClassName()
        Returns the best information about the class of this page that is known during First-Use Assembly.
        Returns:
        actual or declared class of this page, or an empty String if this page is classless, or null if no information about the class of this page is available.

      • isExactClass

        boolean isExactClass()
        Indicates whether the value returned by getClassName() is the actual class of this page, or only a defined constraint on its class.
        Returns:
        true if the class of this page should match the value returned by getClassName; false if the class of this page should derive from, but might not match, the value returned by getClassName, or if getClassName returns null.

      • isParameter

        boolean isParameter()
        Indicates whether the page is defined as a "parameter" to the Rule rather than being an explicit page reference.
        Returns:
        true if page is referenced in the Rule's parameter list.

      • getMatchType

        char getMatchType()
        Returns the match type of the page name found in the Page and Classes tab.
        Returns:
        char Allowed values are: FUAPagesAndClassesHelper.MATCH_NOT_FOUND FUAPagesAndClassesHelper.MATCH_EXACT FUAPagesAndClassesHelper.MATCH_PREFIX

      • getMatchSegments

        int getMatchSegments()
        Returns the number of segments of a reference that were matched during Pages and Classes lookup
        Returns:
        number of segments
